            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Deployment Considerations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Stdio vs HTTP+SSE"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": stdio is simplest for local use. Choose HTTP+SSE when the server runs on a remote host or must serve multiple clients concurrently."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Startup cost"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": stdio servers are started fresh per client connection (each "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "async with stdio_client(...)"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " block). Keep startup cheap \u2014 load credentials and module-level state once; don't make API calls at import time."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Concurrency"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": the "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Server.run()"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " loop handles multiple concurrent "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "tools/call"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " requests. If your tool handler does blocking I/O, use "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "asyncio.to_thread()"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " to avoid blocking the event loop."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Versioning"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": the "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "serverInfo.version"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " field in the "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "initialize"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " response lets clients detect schema changes. Increment it whenever you add, remove, or rename tools."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Handling Blocking I/O"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "MCP server handlers run on an asyncio event loop. Synchronous blocking calls (requests.get, file reads, subprocess calls) will block all concurrent tool calls. Wrap them with asyncio.to_thread():"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio, requests\nfrom mcp.server import Server\nfrom mcp import types\n\napp = Server('slow-server')\n\n@app.call_tool()\nasync def call_tool(name: str, arguments: dict) -> list[types.TextContent]:\n    if name == \"run_report\":\n        # requests.get is synchronous \u2014 wrap it to avoid blocking the event loop\n        def _fetch() -> str:\n            resp = requests.get(\n                \"https://slow-api.example.com/report\",\n                params=arguments,\n                timeout=60,\n            )\n            resp.raise_for_status()\n            return resp.json().get('summary', 'No summary')\n\n        summary = await asyncio.to_thread(_fetch)\n        return [types.TextContent(type='text', text=summary)]\n\n    raise ValueError(f'Unknown tool: {name}')\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This is especially important when a single server handles multiple concurrent requests (HTTP+SSE mode). In stdio mode with one client, blocking is less harmful but still a good habit."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Progress Notifications"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For long-running tool calls, servers can stream progress notifications to the host without waiting for the call to complete. The host can surface these to the user or log them:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
